article.headline: Harvard 66, Army 54
article.story: BOSTON -- Jeremy Lin scored 24 points and added five steals to lead Harvard past Army, 66-54, on Saturday. Harvard trailed 32-30 early in the second half, but took the lead for good on a 13-4 run in which Lin scored seven points and also had a block and a steal. Lin shot 6-of-12 from the floor and made all nine of his free throws. Keith Wright had 12 points, 13 rebounds and four blocks for Harvard (3-1), which set a school record with 12 blocked shots. Harvard's Drew Housman scored 11 of his 15 points in the second half. Cleveland Richard had 16 points, six rebounds, four steals and four assists to lead Army (1-5). The Crimson led 29-28 at the break and made 5-of-9 shots from 3-point range the second half after converting just 2-of-12 3-point shots in the first half.
